body:
@moranr With the changed dimensions, I was wondering if the contents would need to be offset to ensure the spacing remained consistent. For instance, with additional vertical space, the contents might be sitting too high since the additional space goes entirely to the bottom. And similarly would need to consider less vertical space and more/less horizontal space.

We're only talking a few pixels here so it's not much. But I know that we've spent a lot of time getting them nodes looking exactly right. Just wanted to ensure that you thought things were still looking good.

WRT the key modifier - Do you have thoughts on which behavior should be the default and which should be activated with Shift?

Here are the size changes that I've made for this feature:
```
     var portDimensions = {
         width: 240,
-        height: 50
+        height: 48
     };
     var remotePortDimensions = {
         width: 240,
-        height: 75
+        height: 80
     };
// process-group
     var dimensions = {
-        width: 380,
-        height: 172
+        width: 384,
+        height: 176
     };

// remote process group
     var dimensions = {
-        width: 380,
-        height: 158
+        width: 384,
+        height: 176
     };
```

Luckily, I didn't have to make drastic changes to accommodate the 8-pixel snap alignment.  The most drastic shift is clearly the Remote Process Group's height.  I scrolled in a bit to get a closer look (you can ignore the border artifacts - they're from my screenshot utility):

Before:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11933208/53594122-65f10a80-3b57-11e9-8338-528c26443b2c.png)

After:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11933208/53594110-5f629300-3b57-11e9-9384-d5001006eb7b.png)

I think this change warrants a slight adjustment.  The others probably don't need any modifications.

Here's the Process Group component, before and after:

Before:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11933208/53594208-9afd5d00-3b57-11e9-9233-b69200781927.png)

After:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/11933208/53594215-9e90e400-3b57-11e9-8282-259faea8048e.png)

I spent a little time looking over changes and everything I have observed so far looks good. I see the RPG last refresh text I took note of previously has been addressed.

I think this being default behavior will add the greatest value. You can easily align components as you drag/drop or move them on the canvas, creating straight connection lines w/o having to go through the context menu. It also lets you align along a single horizontal or vertical edge (e.g., align left, align top) which currently is not possible. Disabling the behavior  in my opinion  would rarely be used going forward when building new flows. However, using the Shift key to do so is very easy.

@mcgilman / @andrewmlim hopefully you all have some time to try it out to see how you like it, plus more eyes to identify any issues due to size changes would be great.

@R-Bower thanks for all your work on this!

Sorry for the delay getting back here. 

@moranr It looks like the dimensions of the Remote Process Group changed to match the height of the Process Group. This change was a little more pronounced than others. See the screenshot below.

<img width="868" alt="Screen Shot 2019-03-08 at 2 40 53 PM" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/123395/54051615-36be4700-41b0-11e9-896b-7a217e1e8375.png">

@R-Bower The second and third (revert commit) has some merge conflicts with current master. I can sort of work through those but the resulting commit shows a lot of files changed where their contents are identical. I was wondering if you might be able to rebase and force push this PR without these two present. I might be able to drop these while I'm doing an interactive rebase assuming there are no additional changes needed here.

@R-Bower Ok, sounds like we're good with the component dimensions. However, I did notice one small issue. In `nf-connection.js` we've adjusted the run status and expiration icons. I think we need to also update the load balancing icons [1]. Since the others were bumped by 8 pixels (200 -> 208) I think we'd need to adjust these by the same increment. This icon is only available when in clustered mode. Let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks!

[1] https://github.com/apache/nifi/blob/master/nifi-nar-bundles/nifi-framework-bundle/nifi-framework/nifi-web/nifi-web-ui/src/main/webapp/js/nf/canvas/nf-connection.js#L1384

@bbende I've updated ConsumeKafka_2_0, ConsumeKafkaRecord_2_0, PublishKafka_2_0, and PublishKakaRecord_2_0 documents regarding SASL configurations that I came across.

Will explore more and keep contributing. Your blogs on NiFi are my goto guide ever since I started off.
Thank you.

